        "itemDescription": "The city used eminent domain  to demolish homes in order to accommodate the expansion of the Dome area to provide venues and parking for the 1996 Olympics.  Although the city made much of public/private partnerships to improve the neighborhoods around Olympic Park, residents once again felt let down by the gap between the promises made and the outcome of events. This picture is of Columbus Ward, long-time community activist in the neighborhoods just south of the Westside Peoplestown, Mechanicsville and Summerhill, where two Domes and Olympic-era development made similar promises of urban redevelopment. Ward questions whether the television coverage of the Olympics would also zoom in on the living conditions in the neighborhoods around the stadiums. ",
